# 2p_secondary_fire — client. P09 RMB sync test.
#
# Pairs with 2p_secondary_fire.host.shot. The client carries Pulse Rifle
# (primary) + Grappling Hook (secondary) and RMB-fires the hook. The
# host carries Frag Grenades secondary and RMB-throws one; the client
# should see the host's incoming grenade (FIRE_EVENT replicates).
#
# What the client log should show:
#   - t=170 mech=N fire_secondary edge active=0 prim=0 sec=13 cd=...
#   - t=170 grapple_fire(RMB) ph=N        (server fires for the client)
#   - The client's local view spawns a visual PROJ_GRAPPLE_HEAD (kind=10)
#     via the FIRE_EVENT reply — this was the missing piece that made
#     the grapple "disappear" in P09's first ship.

window 1280 720
out build/shots/net/2p_secondary_fire_client
network connect 127.0.0.1:24091
name ClientB

loadout - "Pulse Rifle" "Grappling Hook" Light Standard

# Match host's peer_spawn so we predict from the right starting point.
spawn_at 2540 984

# Aim at the host's chest (300 px to the left).
aim 2240 956

at 130 shot t130_pre_match

# Host throws its grenade at script tick 140 — client should see it
# incoming around tick 155.
at 155 shot t155_incoming_grenade

# T=200-208: client RMB-holds → Grappling Hook fires. Active slot
# stays primary (Pulse Rifle); the grapple head flies left toward
# the host. Held for 8 ticks for the same input-durability reason as
# the host script.
at 200 press fire_secondary
at 208 release fire_secondary
at 215 shot t215_grapple_outgoing

at 260 shot t260_aftermath

at 320 end
